Definition: turn abruptly and face the other way, either physically or metaphorically
Example: He turned around to face his opponent; My conscience told me to turn around before I made a mistake
Synonyms: swing_about, turn_around, noun, event, turn, abruptly, and, face, the, other, way, either, physically, or, metaphorically, He, turned, around, to, his, opponent, My, conscience, told, me, before, I, made, a, mistake
Frame: 1,2
Category: verb.motion
